# Project Pre-requisites

## Overview

This task lists the software tools and Python libraries required to develop the **A Comprehensive Measure of Well-Being (HDI Prediction System)**. These technologies support data preprocessing, machine learning, visualization, and web application deployment.

---

## Required Software

- Anaconda Navigator
- PyCharm IDE

---

## Required Python Libraries

- NumPy
- Pandas
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Flask

---

## Official Links

| Tool | Link |
|------|------|
| Anaconda Navigator | https://www.anaconda.com/download |
| PyCharm | https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/ |
| NumPy | https://numpy.org/doc/stable/ |
| Pandas | https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/ |
| Scikit-learn | https://scikit-learn.org/stable/ |
| Matplotlib | https://matplotlib.org/stable/ |
| Seaborn | https://seaborn.pydata.org/ |
| Flask | https://flask.palletsprojects.com/ |

---

## Outcome

Successfully identified and documented all required software tools and libraries needed to build, train, and deploy the HDI Prediction System.

---

## Result

The project environment is fully prepared for machine learning development, data visualization, and Flask-based deployment.
